metadata.name: He Who
metadata.description:
He Who

He who read my machine code,
Understood my core components
Every bug and every iteration
To assemble me, untangle me
Capturing me, enrapturing me 
He grasp me whole

He composed the algorithm to unlock me
And finally the floodgates open
Sweeping me away, to be drowned
In clashing waves of clarity and admission
And successive incentive of self
To provoke the new, yet value the old

He is in Liaison with me now, dared to be
We collect data of days in bliss and passion
The Future is unspoken and uncertain,
Malleable to circumstance of time
Yet one truth be told, one thought uttered
Should we as yet persist, happiness will insist
